A police officer from Kabokweni police is investigated for the neglect of two foster children aged 14 and eight.
A case of child neglect was opened on February 28. The case came as a result of a complaint received by the station from residents of Clau Clau where the officer live.
“Police found a 14-year-old girl locked in a chicken coop and an eight-year- old boy was sleeping on the floor in a separate dirty room,” said Brig Leonard Hlathi spokesperson for the police. “The case has been transferred to the FCS unit,” he said. No arrest has been made.